subSubSection.paragraph:
Male (
Fig. 14
). Labrum transverse, anterior margin widely shallowly incised. Head lustrous, anterior part of head and vertex covered with fine punctures, frons with larger punctures. Head surface almost glabrous, the short hairs visible only along the inner margins of eyes. Frons broad, 2.25–2.44 times as wide as the diameter of the eye, with an indistinct shallow impression in the middle. Antennomere 1 moderately clavate, antennomere 4 triangular, antennae distinctly serrated from segment 5 .
